  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0ba3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A new phone number to inquire about train services",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka has taken steps to introduce an emergency telephone number for passengers to easily communicate with the Railways Department.",
        "Passengers wishing to contact the department for any queries regarding train services, train schedules or other related information can contact the number 1971 anytime.",
        "People can contact the department in three languages \u200b\u200b(Sinhala, Tamil and English).",
        "People can get information like train service timetables, seat reservations, train fares, contact railway security services and issues related to train passes.",
        "The new 24-hour emergency number 1971 will be operational tomorrow (14) after 7.00 am."
      ],
